---
description: Module services — class-based services, naming, placement under src/modules/[name]/services, dependency injection.
globs:
  - "**/*.service.ts"
alwaysApply: false
---

- a service should always live as part of a module, and be located at: `./src/modules/[name]/services/`
- a service file must be named: `[name].service.ts`
- never create a service as a function. always as a class.
- a service receives its **specific dependencies** as constructor arguments (e.g. a repository, `TopicPublisherService`, `LoggerService`). Do NOT inject the whole `app: Application` object into a service — that is reserved for controllers and middlewares.
- a service can only be instantiated by its domain module main class, under which it lives.
